developerResponse:
{'id': 20611128, 'body': "Hi there Ana!

Yes, you are describing what so many with anxiety and panic attacks unfortunately go through. We're so happy that you found Rootd and that you can feel more confident having this knowledge under your belt. Thanks so much for leaving this thoughtful review so that others experiencing what you were can see that there is a solution out there.
All the best! ", 'modified': '2021-01-24T19:38:16Z'}

{'id': 21997097, 'body': 'Thank you very much for your review. We just released a new app update today with new guided visualization, a brand new check-in tool, and more. Please check it out!

We’re constantly working on more updates, and definitely plan to add more lessons - but we’re a very small team working nights and weekends to move as quickly as possible. 

Every review makes a huge difference for whether or not other users find Rootd - so we appreciate yours and would LOVE to makes it to 5 stars. Please email us at team@rootd.io, we’d love to hear more 🙏', 'modified': '2021-04-01T15:20:13Z'}

{'id': 15450604, 'body': "Thank you for the lovely review, Miklayla! 

We're so glad Rootd is there for you. Let us know if you ever have any questions by emailing us at team@rootd.io! 

All the best on your journey! ", 'modified': '2020-05-20T16:43:00Z'}

{'id': 22879788, 'body': "UPDATE:

We are still waiting for your email at support@rootd.io. We can solve this for your immediately once you let us know which account is yours (we don't have the ability to find who you are on our end, for privacy reasons) so please reach out :)

Hello. We’re sorry to hear about this issue and we’d like to help fix it asap. Could you please email us at team@rootd.io?", 'modified': '2021-05-18T16:13:16Z'}

{'id': 18483307, 'body': 'Hi! We release new and improved free content every month. The following are all already in the app and completely free: the Rootr panic button, understanding lessons, Breathr deep breathing, 2 min visualization, emergency contact, stats page, and anxiety journal. 

We’re a very small team and every review makes a big difference, please let us how we can help make your review a 5 star. 

Please email us at team@rootd.io ', 'modified': '2020-10-14T17:44:37Z'}

{'id': 15930530, 'body': "Hi Jasmine, 

The emergency helpline tool is there for emergencies when it can feel like nothing else is helping. We include this button because there are a lot of young people that use Rootd and we want to ensure them that there should be no stigma around asking for help! You can also include the number of a friend or family member in this place if that feels more comfortable for you. 

Please send us an email to team@rootd.io for more instruction and explanation on how the app works. We'd love for you to get the same benefits hundreds of thousands of other Rootd users get from the app. All the best to you! We look forward to your email. Again, our email is team@rootd.io", 'modified': '2020-06-11T18:40:00Z'}

{'id': 18387361, 'body': "Hi Emma, 

We are a very small team working our hardest on this after having experienced panic attacks and anxiety ourselves. We take our user feedback extremely seriously (and is why we put in the vibration - it was requested by users). It would mean a lot if you gave us the chance to change this review from a 1 star to 5 stars :) Please email us at team@rootd.io (we aren't able to know what your email is so we can't email you). 

Looking forward to connecting and fixing this issue for you! ", 'modified': '2020-10-10T01:54:43Z'}

{'id': 19881288, 'body': "Hi there Rae, 
Were you able to hear back from one of us? If not, please email team@rootd.io

We'd really love to provide you a 5 star experience as our ratings are very important for us as a small team. They help others that could benefit from it find the app :) ", 'modified': '2020-12-20T17:32:41Z'}

{'id': 14221568, 'body': 'Hi there, 

It looks like you may have not read the lesson on the Rootr tool (big red button). It explains that the yellow / challenging option should be used when you're ready to face the anxiety head on in the midst of a panic attack. Until then, you should use the other calming option. This tool was carefully planned out and based on Cognitive Behavioural Therapy, helping many "graduate" from panic attacks and using the Rootd app. That being said, it should be used according to the instructions. Please email us at team@rootd.io as we'd love to hear more! 

Thank you ', 'modified': '2020-03-24T18:57:38Z'}

{'id': 13497259, 'body': "Hi there,

You must have a new version of the iPhone :) 

We are currently fixing this issue and the update should be out in a few days. Please email team@rootd.io so we can help get you signed up, and we'd be happy to offer you something in return due to this inconvenience. ", 'modified': '2020-02-14T22:25:25Z'}
